Sentencas: A high-entropy alloy coating of FeCoNiMnCu was prepared on SUS 430 steel via magnetron sputtering for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnects application.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: The coated steels were subject to thermal exposure in air at 800 degrees C for up to 10 weeks.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Phase constituents, microstructure and area specific resistance (ASR) of the coated steel before and after the oxidation testing were investigated.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Results indicated the alloy coating was thermally converted into a high-entropy spinel coating of (Fe,Co,Ni,Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 after oxidation and a protective Cr2O3 layer was formed at the steel/coating interface.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: The (Fe,Co,Ni,Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 spinel coating effectively suppressed growth of Cr2O3 layer and outward diffusion of Cr during the long term exposure.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Scale ASR of the coated steel was as low as 6.59 m Omega.cm(2) at 800 degrees C after 10 weeks.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: It indicates that (Fe,Co,Ni,Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 is a promising coating material for SOFC metallic interconnects.
Titulo: High-entropy FeCoNiMnCu alloy coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects
